- "Shine like beacons of success" refers to the top-performing clubs that stand out in terms of their performance and financial metrics;
- The financial metrics (revenue, expenses, profit) are averaged across the league to provide a benchmark for the top-performing clubs.

sql:
SELECT nationality, COUNT(coach_id) AS number_of_coaches
FROM coaches
GROUP BY nationality;

external_knowledge:
- "blossomed" refers to a positive improvement or growth in performance;
- "points" in football typically refer to the total points accumulated by a club over a season;
- "Ligue 1" is the top French professional football league for men's clubs.

- "stands tall" refers to the club having the largest stadium capacity;
- "most victories compared to runner-up finishes" means the club has won more times than it has been a runner-up;
- "grandest stadium" refers to the stadium with the highest capacity;
- "guiding light for more than five years" refers to the coach with the longest tenure of more than five years.

- "stands tall like a giant" refers to the club with the highest profit;
- "reaping the most financial rewards" refers to the club with the highest total revenue minus total expenses;
- "titan" is another metaphorical term for the club with the highest profit;
- "matches played as the home team" refers to the number of matches where the club was the home team.

sql:
SELECT club_name
FROM clubs
WHERE stadium_capacity > (SELECT AVG(stadium_capacity) FROM clubs);

SELECT season, goals_scored, points
FROM performances
ORDER BY points DESC;

external_knowledge:
