- "holds the throne" symbolizes being the top-ranked or leading nation;
- "the test of time" indicates a minimum participation of six seasons;
- "the sweet nectar of victory" signifies winning at least one championship.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT club_id) AS total_champions
FROM performances
WHERE position = 'winner';

external_knowledge:
- 'shining star' refers to the club with the highest profit;
- '1955/1956 season' is a specific period in football history;
- 'profit' refers to the financial gain.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.club_name) AS total_clubs
FROM performances p
JOIN clubs c ON p.club_id = c.club_id;

